{"TopicId":149997,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.9.x] EVA Enhancements Continued","CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-14T17:25:40Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-14T17:25:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is a revival/continuation of the old EVA Enhancements mod\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\nThe new version for KSP 1.4.1 has new dependencies\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cu\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:24px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#c0392b;\u0022\u003ENew Dependencies\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/u\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/170747-141-click-through-blocker/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022 style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#3d6594;\u0022\u003EClick Through Blocker\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/169509-141-toolbar-controller-for-modders/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022 style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#3d6594;\u0022\u003EToolbarController\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cabbr style=\u0022border-bottom:none;\u0022 title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Ehas been updated to install the dependencies, if needed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nDownload:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022http://spacedock.info/mod/994/EVA%20Enhancements%20Continued\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://spacedock.info/mod/994/EVA Enhancements Continued\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nSource:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/linuxgurugamer/EVAEnhancementsContinued\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/linuxgurugamer/EVAEnhancementsContinued\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nLicense: MIT\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.patreon.com/linuxgurugamer\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022color:rgb(60,105,148);text-decoration:underline;background-color:transparent;\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Patreon.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://bayerfamily.net/Patreon.png\u0022 style=\u0022vertical-align:middle;border:0px;height:82px;width:300px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.patreon.com/linuxgurugamer\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022color:rgb(60,105,148);text-decoration:underline;background-color:transparent;\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.patreon.com/linuxgurugamer\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/a/o33Xx\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://imgur.com/a/o33Xx\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong style=\u0022font-weight:bold;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-decoration:underline;\u0022\u003ECurrent Features\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\nKerbal profession and level is now visible in the right-click action menu. No more wondering if Frolie Kerman is supposed to be an engineer or a scientist.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\nPitch and roll can now be controlled with the keyboard. No more awkward mouse clicking and dragging... you can now do backflips and cartwheels on the Mun! By default the controls are mapped as follows:\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);margin-left:80px;\u0022\u003E\nPitch Down - Alpha2\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);margin-left:80px;\u0022\u003E\nPitch Up - X\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);margin-left:80px;\u0022\u003E\nRoll Left - Z\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);margin-left:80px;\u0022\u003E\nRoll Right - C\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\nI have found these work well in conjunction with the standard WASDQE controls (while letting you keep your right hand on the mouse for camera control). If you wish to remap them you can use the \u0022Settings\u0022 window, accessible from the stock application launcher or Blizzy78\u0027s toolbar.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\nthe EVA \u0022rotate on camera move\u0022 setting can now be toggled any time by hitting the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E toggle (default T). Enabling it can make some EVA navigation a bit easier, but disabling it gives you more control.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\njetpack power can now be modified any time through a slider in the EVA right-click action menu. Fuel usage is scaled accordingly. \u00A0Both max and fine control power can be modified.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\nthe default and the fine control jetpack power level can be set via the \u0022Settings\u0022 window.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\nprecision controls can now be toggled using the same key as in normal flight mode (default is CapsLock). This automatically sets your jetpack power to 10% for finer control.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\nfinally, some Nav Ball customizations for EVA mode. The throttle gauge will display your current jetpack power level between 0 and 100%. \u003Cs\u003EThe \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E indicator will light to show your if jetpack is enabled.\u003C/s\u003E\u00A0 (\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E indicator light is now a stock feature) The \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E indicator will light to show if \u0022rotate on move\u0022 is enabled (only if the jetpack is on though).\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\nAdded setting to allow/disallow EVA kerbal from filling EVA propellent from the pod\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\nOption to allow Navball follow kerbal on EVA\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\nAdded navball fix to settings screen\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nAdded option to disable Navball markers on EVA\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nAdded ability to use a modifier key with a regular key (but disables the ability to use the mod key by itself). \u00A0On Windows, the key is ALT\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-04-08T00:51:43Z\u0022 title=\u002204/08/2018 12:51  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EApril 8, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by linuxgurugamer\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Flayer","CreatedById":109391,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-14T17:31:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny plans to make EVA utilize a limited amount of fuel available in the command pod, or alternatively having an option to disable the automatic EVA refuel?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ser","CreatedById":104207,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-14T17:35:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222804055\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476466302\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022109391\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Flayer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Flayer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny plans to make EVA utilize a limited amount of fuel available in the command pod, or alternatively having an option to disable the automatic EVA refuel?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://spacedock.info/mod/623/EvaFuel\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EEvaFuel\u003C/a\u003E?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-14T18:51:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222804055\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476466302\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022109391\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Flayer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Flayer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny plans to make EVA utilize a limited amount of fuel available in the command pod, or alternatively having an option to disable the automatic EVA refuel?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cs\u003ENot at this time, but go ahead and make a github issue\u003C/s\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSince there is a mod specifically for that, I probably won\u0027t bother adding it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-10-14T18:53:21Z\u0022 title=\u002210/14/2016 06:53  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 14, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by linuxgurugamer\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bombaatu","CreatedById":157643,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-14T19:36:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou have the thruster power controlled by a right-click menu item; have you considered using the throttle controls instead (or in addition)?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBTW, THANK YOU\u00A0for bring this back!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Flayer","CreatedById":109391,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-14T19:44:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222804063\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476466524\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022104207\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Ser\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Ser said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://spacedock.info/mod/623/EvaFuel\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EEvaFuel\u003C/a\u003E?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh thanks, I probably should have looked for myself since last time I hunted for one was over a year ago, my bad.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JeffreyCor","CreatedById":93167,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-15T01:28:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDownloaded from Spacedock. The toolbar icon is a blank white square. Looking good otherwise, I\u0027ve missed this mod for my EVAs \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"doggonemess","CreatedById":160106,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-15T10:01:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSlight little goof - the link in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E points to the wrong location. It should be\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003Ehttp://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/149997-12-eva-enhancements-continued/\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-15T12:09:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222804912\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476494889\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002293167\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JeffreyCor\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, JeffreyCor said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDownloaded from Spacedock. The toolbar icon is a blank white square. Looking good otherwise, I\u0027ve missed this mod for my EVAs \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFixed\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222805330\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476525677\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022160106\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022doggonemess\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, doggonemess said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSlight little goof - the link in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E points to the wrong location. It should be\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003Ehttp\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022com\u0022\u003E//forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/149997-12-eva-enhancements-continued/\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFixed in Spacedock, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E will pick it up soon\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Warezcrawler","CreatedById":145377,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-29T18:53:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI love that this mod have been revived!!! I missed it in 1.1.3, and I even tried fixing it myself (failed that is!!!)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTHANKS A LOT linuxgurugamer!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gianni1122","CreatedById":170752,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-30T17:11:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve always enjoyed this mod. Thanks for continuing. I have a possible suggestion,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfter either pitching or rolling, the game automatically\u00A0applies\u00A0thrust to \u0022correct/counter\u0022 the players \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E input. I should also mention that the stock game does this as well when you use the Q or E key while on EVA.\u00A0This is an EXTREMELY annoying occurrence for anyone who wants full control of there kerbal on EVA. I assume some people who use this mod would agree.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf there was a way to turn this off, my immersive EVA experience would be complete...\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022129964\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@linuxgurugamer\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0I\u0027ve seen you on several mod forum threads so I know your busy. I appreciate your consideration but understand you may not have time. Cheers\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-30T17:38:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe applied thrust is meant to stop your movement. \u00A0I\u0027m not sure if that can be stopped, but I\u0027ll take a look. \u00A0it will ave to a configurable option, I don\u0027t want to change the current mode\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gianni1122","CreatedById":170752,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-30T20:21:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222830570\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221477849126\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe applied thrust is meant to stop your movement. \u00A0I\u0027m not sure if that can be stopped, but I\u0027ll take a look. \u00A0it will ave to a configurable option, I don\u0027t want to change the current mode\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA configurable option would be perfect.\u00A0Thanks for\u00A0looking into it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gianni1122","CreatedById":170752,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-02T19:58:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d also like to mention that while using precision mode on eva, this auto applied thrust feature COMPLETELY fails after Q or E is used.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-02T21:00:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222835366\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221478116709\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022170752\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gianni1122\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Gianni1122 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d also like to mention that while using precision mode on eva, this auto applied thrust feature COMPLETELY fails after Q or E is used.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFails, as in it isn\u0027t applied, or it goes wonky, or what?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gianni1122","CreatedById":170752,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-02T21:17:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222835446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221478120421\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 minutes ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFails, as in it isn\u0027t applied, or it goes wonky, or what?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry. Fails as in it goes wonky. After Q or E input the kerbal endlessly tries to auto correct itself (unsuccessfully as far as I can tell)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo recreate, go eva, turn on \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003Ercs\u003C/abbr\u003E, turn on precision controls, rotate with Q/E, kerbal will-on its own-proceed to rotate left to right\u00A0unable to correct/stabilize\u00A0itself.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust confirmed this occurs with EvaEnhancents added keys\u00A0as well. Honestly you should just try it. Wonky is an understatement lol.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-11-02T21:18:31Z\u0022 title=\u002211/02/2016 09:18  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 2, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Gianni1122\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-02T21:31:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m at work right now, so this will help when I get home\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-03T01:51:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222835366\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221478116709\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022170752\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gianni1122\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Gianni1122 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d also like to mention that while using precision mode on eva, this auto applied thrust feature COMPLETELY fails after Q or E is used.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk. \u00A0What\u0027s happening is that the autocorrect code can\u0027t adjust for the low level of the thrusters. \u00A0If you simply go out of precision mode when done for a few seconds, it will work properly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t think I can do anything about that, but I am going to look into seeing if I can disable that totally, especially when in precision mode.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTry increasing the Default Precision Jetpack Power to 50%, the 10% seems to be too low for the self-correcting code to deal with. \u00A0It worked for me at 50%\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-11-03T01:56:16Z\u0022 title=\u002211/03/2016 01:56  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 3, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by linuxgurugamer\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DStaal","CreatedById":155685,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-03T01:57:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGlad to have this back - It\u0027s nice to have full three-axis control of my Kerbals on EVA.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-03T02:08:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve found that the setting the EVA thrust level to 25% allows the auto-thrust to work properly. \u00A0That will be in the next update\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gianni1122","CreatedById":170752,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-03T04:12:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222835829\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221478137902\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t think I can do anything about that, but I am going to look into seeing if I can disable that totally, especially when in precision mode.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooking forward to seeing what you come up with.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222835845\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221478138895\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve found that the setting the EVA thrust level to 25% allows the auto-thrust to work properly. \u00A0That will be in the next update\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll try dropping the limiter to 25. Cheers\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-03T10:44:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat I did notice is that if you spin too much while under power, then the game can get confused. \u00A0Just like a real person :-)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo what you do is to get out of Precision mode for a few seconds, then go back in\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBeyond that, I spent a few hours on this last night, and unfortunately, the code is unavailable to mods, so you are going to have to live with this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gianni1122","CreatedById":170752,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-03T18:51:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222836218\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221478169864\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat I did notice is that if you spin too much while under power, then the game can get confused. \u00A0Just like a real person :-)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo what you do is to get out of Precision mode for a few seconds, then go back in\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBeyond that, I spent a few hours on this last night, and unfortunately, the code is unavailable to mods, so you are going to have to live with this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBummer :-/\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI appreciate you having a look. I\u0027m thoroughly enjoying\u00A0the mods you\u0027re maintaining.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you think I should I bother Squad about the game\u0027s\u00A0inability to handle precision mode on eva?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-03T18:57:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, because that is a function of the mod, not normal EVA\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"COL.R.Neville","CreatedById":168067,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-03T19:26:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthat going nuts and burning up all the mono on eva is a stock ksp thing. eva kerbals have like their own \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003Esas\u003C/abbr\u003E now so just hit the f button a time or two and it will quit doing ti.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}